    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your<strong> garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-pesto-mac-n-cheese/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>macaroni</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the macaroni for 7-9 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>cooked macaroni </strong>and set aside until later</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-pesto-mac-n-cheese/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[25g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms \u2013 this is your<strong> roux</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-pesto-mac-n-cheese/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Gradually whisk 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> into the roux, a little at a time, and cook for 5-6 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains \u2013 this is your <strong>b\u00e9chamel sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-pesto-mac-n-cheese/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Combine 1/4 of your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for later!) with your <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>and<strong> </strong>a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>in a bowl<strong> </strong>\u2013 these are your <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-pesto-mac-n-cheese/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash your <strong>spinach </strong>then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong> and <strong>drained macaroni</strong> to the pan with the<strong> b\u00e9chamel sauce</strong></p><p>Stir through your<strong> traditional Italian pesto</strong>, <strong>grated cheddar</strong> and<strong> remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up until the cheese has melted and the spinach has wilted</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-pesto-mac-n-cheese/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Transfer the mixture to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs</strong> followed by your<strong> smoked streaky bacon </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 20-25 min or until it is golden and bubbling and the bacon is crisp \u2013 this is your <strong>bacon & pesto mac 'n' cheese</strong></p><p>Tip: Put the dish on the top shelf of the oven to help crisp up the bacon!</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-pesto-mac-n-cheese/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dress the <strong>salad</strong> with your <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Serve your <strong>bacon & pesto mac 'n' cheese</strong> with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and the <strong>dressed salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
